         <BLOCKQUOTE id=quote><font size=1 face="Verdana, Arial, Helvetica" id=quote>quote:<hr height=1 noshade id=quote>Saleem, I know the power of a 60 Shaman. See the thing is most shamans have zero clue as to how to PvP.<hr height=1 noshade id=quote></BLOCKQUOTE id=quote></font id=quote><font face="Verdana, Arial, Helvetica" size=2 id=quote></P><P>90% of all classes have zero clue how to PvP :P</P><P>Cerilius, I'd like to draw your attention to a few different spells here.  The first one is called Manaskin.  Not quite as good as Rune V, but two can play that game eh?  Secondly, assuming he prepared his buff list properly, throw in a quick siphon strength, and then dot the fuck out of him.  You fill up his #1 buff slot and suddenly he has to dispell his own buffs just to get at your dot.  You can have him re-pyroed/re siphoned in the time it takes annul magic to repop.  If he was smart enough to leave 2 slots empty...no problem, use ShadowVortex too.  Pyro/Pyre+Splurt are more than enough to finish him rune and all.  While he frantically dispells himself, you Touch of Night. End of Enchanter.  Oh and another fun tactic...see how well your chanter buddy knows the game by Harmshielding at the beginning of the fight...if he doesn't recognize the spell effect, first thing he's gonna do in all likelihood is tash you...see if he notices.  INVUL people don't generate a resist message.  GL with those nancyboy nukes without tash, chantaman.</P><P>Same dot strat will put you all over any druid.  Unlike the mighty Shaman, druid heals suck ass.  You can run him oom pretty easy.  Considering a druid is going to hit me about as often/hard as a level1 rat in west freeport...I really don't see why they'd bother to melee.  I like how you assume a druid can insta poof the pet or something...you can dispell your pet just like you can dispell yourself.  You have Arch Lich for mana...druid has PoTG.  If the druid has no brain, dispell any dots out of your first buff slot that he throws on you.  If he magically has a brain, he'll get Winged Death on you sooner or later...best PvP DOT in the game.  That's when you stack Vexing and Bond on him and laugh.</P><P>-Saleem<BR>Warlock of Xegony</P><P>Edited by - Saleem on 06/06/2002  22:41:44<a href="#top"><img src="icon_go_up.gif" height="15" width="15" border="0" align="right" alt="Go to Top of Page"></a></font></td>
