         <BLOCKQUOTE id=quote><font size=1 face="Verdana, Arial, Helvetica" id=quote>quote:<hr height=1 noshade id=quote>RuneV costs 350 mana, and you are regenerating mana around twice as fast as the enchanter.<hr height=1 noshade id=quote></BLOCKQUOTE id=quote></font id=quote><font face="Verdana, Arial, Helvetica" size=2 id=quote></P><P>An enchanter's first objective in PvP against any caster isn't doing damage. Instead, he's going to begin the fight by ignoring your Manaskin and tapping your mana pool dry (with Mana Sieve and Theft of Thought). Once you're out of mana, you can cast Lich to regen some more, but you'll lose HP at the same time, and by the time you have enough mana to bond something, the enchanter will have tapped you again. (Also, keep in mind that Mana Sieve only costs 150 mana and the enchanter has Clarity II. Running out of mana isn't an issue for him.)</P><P>It might also be worthwhile for you to do some calculations with Lich and Vexing, and compare the overall mana regen you'd get from using both to Clarity II. I think you'll be surprised.</P><P>Cerilius D`Nixx<BR>54 Necromancer, VZ<a href="#top"><img src="icon_go_up.gif" height="15" width="15" border="0" align="right" alt="Go to Top of Page"></a></font></td>
