         Take it from a guy who's beaten his fair share of (non tard) 60 Enchanters...(more than a few before I was even 60) once you isolate RuneV and dispell it, or you dot it out of effectiveness, he's going to lose the HP game.  This is long before you're oom from his sieving.</P><P>Enchanters cannot heal themselves, they can only hope to mitigate damage with runes.  They also regen mana half as fast as you, the math works out no matter how you look at it.  If all he did was sieve, he could take 400 mana every 11 seconds.  Consider...I have 3200 mana.  Can you inflict 1800 (high estimate of enchanter's hp + RuneV) damage in 88 seconds (worst case scenario)? I can.</P><P>-Saleem<BR>Warlock of Xegony</P><P>Edited by - Saleem on 06/07/2002  14:33:22<a href="#top"><img src="icon_go_up.gif" height="15" width="15" border="0" align="right" alt="Go to Top of Page"></a></font></td>
