         Cerilius obviously belongs to those 90% who can't pvp. And enchanter is PATHETIC in PvP, unless he is in the right zone. For now, let's assume this is all taking place in the arena.</P><P>First of all, even assuming that the ench drains the necro oom and that the necro doesn't hurt the enchanter at all throught the whole time (lol yeah good one); assuming this, what's an enchanter going to do next? Melee the necro to death? I got dibs on the necro in that case.</P><P>Second, lets say the enchanter's last buff is rune 5, and he has 2 slots open and has 2 instaclick items. First off, chances are that the enchanter doesn't have cancel magic memorized, instead he has recant. You quickly pop off some debufs, 3 in a row, the enchanter (if using cancel) dispells one but the other two fill up the slots and you can debuff or dot at will then. If he uses recant (much more likely) he will start taking off his own buffs. Remember, while he is doing all that you are free to do whatever you want -- dot some more or get a pet. As to the enchanter poofing the pet, that can take up to 8 minutes.</P><P>So the enchanter tries to cast on the pet, and you know what that gives you? More time. You can cast Pyre on him, and now he will start losing HP very noticebly. While he is trying to mez/root the pet, you keep casting dots, so your last dots are definetly in the last slots. So he has to dispell himself. Chances are he'll click off every buff he can and the chain-recant, right? Well, this all takes time, and that gives you time to dot some more or maybe even dispell the pet, or ToN the enchanter since he has dispelled his rune.</P><P>Notice, throughout this whole time the enchanter didn't have a moment to spare for a mana sieve, let alone refresh bedlam/rune. And you are saying that the enchanter will win.</P><P>Well all I can say is, thanks to people like Cerilius and Potus, people expect the necro to suck. Good thing, it makes it all the more easier for me to win.</P><P>Necro on Vallon Zek<BR>There is no cow level.<a href="#top"><img src="icon_go_up.gif" height="15" width="15" border="0" align="right" alt="Go to Top of Page"></a></font></td>
