         Well, the enchanter is going to charmsploit and poof the pet of course, so it isn't really even a factor...however, I have a pet focus and that puts the pet at a little bit faster than jboot speed.  ie if chanterman doesn't know about charmsploit, he's in for a world of hurt.</P><P><BLOCKQUOTE id=quote><font size=1 face="Verdana, Arial, Helvetica" id=quote>quote:<hr height=1 noshade id=quote>If the enchanter is smart enough to bury Rune V deep within his buffs, and click his instacast items (like jboots, goblin earring, Coldain ring, etc.) after each dispel attempt, then you won't be able to dispel his rune *at all* (not counting sheer luck, where your dispel would skip 10 buffs in a row). As I pointed out in an earlier post, your only hope would be to lifetap through it.<BR><hr height=1 noshade id=quote></BLOCKQUOTE id=quote></font id=quote><font face="Verdana, Arial, Helvetica" size=2 id=quote></P><P>I am quite certain I can dispell and land Shadowvortex and maybe even Siphon before he is able to react by clicking his clickies.  In the real world, insta clicks are quite limited by reaction time.  Hell I might even mem annul and nullify for a chanter duel, that'll take good care of those crap buffs.</P><P><BLOCKQUOTE id=quote><font size=1 face="Verdana, Arial, Helvetica" id=quote>quote:<hr height=1 noshade id=quote>So, a necro's total mana regen would be (assuming Vexing is used as efficienly as possible) = 20 - 26*495/1098 = 8.27 mana per tick.<hr height=1 noshade id=quote></BLOCKQUOTE id=quote></font id=quote><font face="Verdana, Arial, Helvetica" size=2 id=quote></P><P>I want to know what kind of fucking moron uses Vexing against an enchanter playing defensively...use splurt or pyre/pyro.</P><P><BLOCKQUOTE id=quote><font size=1 face="Verdana, Arial, Helvetica" id=quote>quote:<hr height=1 noshade id=quote>Second, necros also get Demi Lich at 60 (31 mana/-36 HP), increasing their regen total to 14.77 mana per tick, about 1.5 times that of the enchanter.<hr height=1 noshade id=quote></BLOCKQUOTE id=quote></font id=quote><font face="Verdana, Arial, Helvetica" size=2 id=quote></P><P>er, I thought I was using Arch Lich for 35mana/-35hp a tick.</P><P><BLOCKQUOTE id=quote><font size=1 face="Verdana, Arial, Helvetica" id=quote>quote:<hr height=1 noshade id=quote>Also, consider that no good enchanter would just stand there waiting for Mana Sieve to refresh. Instead, he would dodge your spells by backing up out of range, waiting through its 8-second recast time before casting it again.<hr height=1 noshade id=quote></BLOCKQUOTE id=quote></font id=quote><font face="Verdana, Arial, Helvetica" size=2 id=quote></P><P>Only an idiot duels without explicitly banning being out of spell range for longer than a certain duration (ie 10 seconds).  If he can run out of range all day, why can't I?  You may as well not even duel if you're going to be heading for opposite ends of the zone.  If you're on a PvP server, fuck with his head...make him come to you, but don't sit there like a gimpass duck while he runs in and out of range.  If I were on a PvP server, and he didn't get the idea after that, he would probably earn a quick gate from me.</P><P>Note that on a PvP server, you are unlikely to be prepared specifically for a chanter duel, and the same goes for him...You most definately have the upper hand in this event.</P><P>I don't recall (and I could be wrong here) very many pieces of chanter gear with innate see invis.  Click your circlet when you see him casting and snicker.  Of course, he probably doesn't know about tab exploit...very few do.  Pressing tab will recover your target, even if the person is invis. (I haven't tested in awhile, they may have fixed this).</P><P>All in all, could a good enchanter beat me once? Probably.  Any class is capable of such an upset.  Could they beat me to 3 or 5? Not a chance.</P><P>I like some of your thinking, Cerilius, but really...get 60. Things change a LOT between 54 and 60.  You've got a lot to learn.</P><P>-Saleem<BR>Warlock of Xegony</P><P><a href="#top"><img src="icon_go_up.gif" height="15" width="15" border="0" align="right" alt="Go to Top of Page"></a></font></td>
