        <hr noshade size="2" color="#545A7D">
        
         Threads like this are pointless.  These two perfect ubergeared level 60s going at it, debuffing each other to fill slots, and waiting for dots so they get full use of their pillage, tucking away every point of mana for a rainy day, blah blah :)</P><P>When I was a level 40 necro in RM, I killed a 54ish druid.  Why?  Because his snares and WD resisted on me, and his snares/roots on my pet resistsed.  Stuff happens, and fights are never these set-piece absurdities you're talking about.</P><P>Obviously everyone on pvp servers who plays a bard or chanter knows about pet-poofing - it's very lame but universal, it even gets done at guild pvp events, bloody waste of bone-chips.</P><P>Anyway, for my two cents, Arch-Lich is conspiciously better than clarity - you need that speed, and there's almost always lots of health coming in from the offense.  If the necro has a nice sow on his pet that could be the end of the story, I know, outside involvement yadayada.  Basically in real life, whichever of these two turkeys got the drop on the other would start winning like crazy - if the nec jumped the chanter, the chanter would probobly not have a good enough rune or a good enough buff order, noone does when they get jumped.  Anyway, so maybe a clever nec leads off with a debuff, but if he's a dope like me he drops a good dot on (pyro, FP, whatever) and chain defluxes.  If chanter is smart he casts gate and the fight is over.  If he is brave and smart maybe he has a good spell lineup, but unless he's got a really nice spell lineup he's taking a couple ticks of the dot, probobly some pet melee eating the hell out of his rune and deflux being cast, so if he stays he'll probobly be dead.  </P><P>If the chanter gets the jump - well, then the necro had better gate, if he can.  Chanter can strip the bejeezus out of his buffs, keep him from getting spells off easily and neutralize any pet that might have been up.  I wouldn't hesitate to SS-Gate, HS-Gate, whatever.  Chanters with the initiative are bad news to low HP people like me.</P><P>Isn't that a little more reasonable?  At least for pvp servers.  Initiative is so important, because the attacked party loses a few beats of timing, doesn't have good spells memmed, doesn't have pet up/buffed, doesn't have the right buffs, in the right order...  And all of that is crucial.  And then there's group pvp, probobly more important than any of this and even less simple to analyze.</P><P>Personally, I'd say this in summation - we Necros have real killing power, and Chanters don't - but chanters can definately kill casters, including unlucky Necros who don't escape when they're in trouble.</P><P>Ulyn Vindix, 53rd, SZ<BR>(Yeah yeah, I'm low.  But I talk to the warlocks, and I've seen enough of these silly "paper battles" to recognize the fallacies.)</P><P> <a href="#top"><img src="icon_go_up.gif" height="15" width="15" border="0" align="right" alt="Go to Top of Page"></a></font></td>
